Vasudeva is the enlightened ferryman who guides Siddhartha to a transcendent understanding of himself and the universe. Vasudeva is spiritually and socially flawless, and he ferries true seekers of wisdom to enlightenment. He is closely linked to the river, and he helps Siddhartha learn how to listen to the riverâ€™s secrets. Siddhartha achieves enlightenment only because of his association with Vasudeva.